<topic id="view-status-information">
  <title>Viewing Status Information</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords><indexterm>Editing XML Documents<indexterm>status
        information</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm product="author developer editor">Information view</indexterm>
        <indexterm product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">Console view</indexterm></keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>Status information generated by <term>schema detection</term>, <term>validation</term>,
        <term>automatic validation</term>, and <term>transformation</term> threads are fed into the
        <uicontrol product="editor author developer">Information</uicontrol>
      <uicontrol product="editorEclipse authorEclipse developerEclipse">Console</uicontrol> view
      allowing you to monitor how the operation is being executed<ph
        product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"> (the <uicontrol>Enable oXygen
          consoles</uicontrol> option must be enabled in the <xref
          href="preferences-view.dita#preferences-view"><uicontrol>View</uicontrol> preferences
          page</xref>)</ph>. </p>
    <fig product="editor author developer">
      <title>Information view messages</title>
      <image href="../img/sa_information_view.png"/>
    </fig>
    <fig product="editorEclipse authorEclipse developerEclipse">
      <title>Console View Messages</title>
      <image href="../img/ec_console_view.png"/>
    </fig>
    <p>Messages contain a timestamp, the name of the thread that generated it and the actual status
      information. The number of displayed messages can be controlled from the <xref
        href="preferences-view.dita"><uicontrol product="author developer editor"
          >Views</uicontrol><uicontrol product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
          >View</uicontrol> preference page</xref>.</p>
    <p>To make the view visible, select <menucascade product="author developer editor">
        <uicontrol>Window</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Show View</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Information</uicontrol>
      </menucascade><menucascade product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">
        <uicontrol>Window</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Show View</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Console</uicontrol>
      </menucascade>.</p>
  </body>
</topic>